==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[larva#Latin|larva]]'' (ghost-like, masked).

====Noun====
{{sb2|'''larva'''|'''[[larvae]] '''or, incorrectly,''' [[larvas]]'''}}

<!--Is the first meaning correct?-->

#A stage of growth for some insects, in which they are wingless and resemble a caterpillar or grub after hatching from their egg
#an animal in the aforementioned stage.
#A form of a recently born or hatched animal that is quite different from its adult stage. 

